Take any picture file
Open in GIMP
Make circular selection
Invert selection
Remove selection
Turn removed selection, now white, to alpha
Export as .png
Reopen in GIMP
Crop Image to Content
Scale to at least 160x160px or any multitude of that
Export and overwrite old .png
Open with Inkscape
Create Circle with Elipse Tool
Set Position to 0,0 and Size to 160,160 or the multitude of resolution of the image
Turn off Fill
Turn on Stroke (color RGBA:00a4e3ff, width 3px times the multitude of resulution of the image)
Export as .png
If you used a multiple of 160x160px as resolution reopen in GIMP and downscale to 160x160
